  <summary>5/26/1988--Introduced.
Expresses the sense of the Congress that the President should establish a special commission on travel and tourism to: (1) study the developed and underdeveloped U.S. travel and tourism markets; and (2) make recommendations to the President and the Congress on ways to increase the U.S. market share of international tourism.</summary>
